<body lang=EN-US style='word-wrap:break-word'>

<div class=WordSection1>

<p  id="заболевание-также-известно-как" class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;line-height:normal'><b><span
style='font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Isthmic-cervical
insufficiency</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>What is isthmic-cervical
insufficiency</span></b></p>

<p id="причины" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Isthmic-cervical insufficiency
is a pathological condition of the cervix that occurs prematurely during
pregnancy, characterized by its painless shortening and expansion.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>The disease is also known as</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>In English, this pathology is
called cervical insufficiency or incompetent cervix</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Causes</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Isthmic-cervical insufficiency usually occurs in the middle of the
second or early third trimester, depending on the severity of the insufficiency.&nbsp;This
condition of the cervix can be congenital or acquired.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>The most common congenital cause is a defect in the embryological
development of the Müllerian ducts.&nbsp;In hereditary connective tissue
dysplasia, which includes conditions such as Ehlers-Danlos syndrome or Marfan
syndrome, collagen deficiency causes the cervix to fail to function properly,
resulting in insufficiency.</span></p>

<p id="кто-в-группе-риска" class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>The most common acquired cause is trauma to the cervix, such as
cervical rupture during childbirth, multiple pregnancy, large fetus or pelvic
proposal, cervical surgery, or cervical dilatation during gynecological
procedures.</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Hormonal changes: low progesterone levels, hyperandrogenism in
polycystic ovary syndrome.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>In many patients, changes in the cervix are the result of
infection/inflammation.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Who is at risk</span></b></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Women who have had a previous cervical injury, such as ruptured
labor, surgery, a large fetus in a previous pregnancy.</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Women who have a congenital predisposition to the development of
isthmic-cervical insufficiency.&nbsp;Such patients may have anatomical
anomalies in the structure of the uterus or congenital connective tissue
dysplasia, in which there is a defect in collagen synthesis.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Obese women.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Pregnant women with iron deficiency anemia.</span></p>

<p  id="как-часто-встречается" class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Women with rheumatological diseases (systemic lupus erythematosus,
rheumatoid arthritis, scleroderma).</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Women with inflammatory diseases of the genital organs (vaginal
infections, chronic endometriosis).</span></p>

<p id="симптомы" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>How often does it occur</span></b></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>According to statistics, the
approximate incidence is 0.5-1% in the general obstetric population and up to
8% in women who have had a history of miscarriages between 12-28 weeks of
pregnancy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Symptoms</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>In the early stages of
pregnancy, isthmic-cervical insufficiency often does not manifest itself in any
way.&nbsp;Some women may have mild discomfort or spotting for several days or
weeks from 14 to 20 weeks pregnant.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Other symptoms include:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>feeling of pressure in the pelvic area;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>pain in the lower back;</span></p>

<p id="диагностика-заболевания" class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>mild abdominal cramps;</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>change in vaginal discharge;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>light vaginal bleeding.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Diagnosis of the
disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Interrogation and
inspection</span></b></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>During the survey, the doctor
collects an anamnesis, a history of gynecological diseases, surgical
interventions on the cervix.&nbsp;If this is not the first pregnancy, then information
is collected on how the previous pregnancy and childbirth proceeded.&nbsp;A
standard gynecological examination is performed, however, a digital examination
is not recommended due to its low information content and an increased risk of
causing premature birth.&nbsp;With severe isthmic-cervical insufficiency,
during examination, the doctor may detect protruding fetal membranes from the
cervical canal.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Laboratory examination</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>To exclude an
infectious-inflammatory process in the vagina, perform:</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>microscopic and microbiological examination of the discharge of
the genital organs,</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>bacteriological urine culture&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=RU
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Functional, radiation
and instrumental diagnostics</span></b></p>

<p id="лечение" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Transvaginal ultrasound&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>is the
main method for diagnosing isthmic-cervical insufficiency.&nbsp;The diagnosis
is established when the shortening of the length of the walls of the cervical
canal (less than 25 mm) or the expansion of the cervical canal (more than 10
mm) is detected.&nbsp;If you have a history of preterm labor or a high risk of cervical
insufficiency, your doctor may order a transvaginal ultrasound every two weeks
from the 16th to the 24th week of pregnancy.&nbsp;With the progression of
insufficiency, surgical treatment is prescribed.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Treatment</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Treatment Goals</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Preservation of pregnancy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Prevention of complications.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Lifestyle and aids</span></b></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>It is recommended to limit:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>physical exercise;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>sexual activity.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Medications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Progesterone.&nbsp;Assign during the 2nd and 3rd trimester of
pregnancy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Procedures</span></b></p>

<p id="возможные-осложнения" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span
lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>An obstetric pessary is a device that reduces the load on the
cervix, creates support for the uterus and prevents premature opening of its
cervix.&nbsp;</span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>The pessary can be installed between 15-30 weeks of pregnancy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Surgery</span></b></p>

<p id="профилактика" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span
lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Cervical cerclage - suturing the cervix.&nbsp;It is performed
before the 24th, in some cases up to the 26th week of pregnancy.&nbsp;The
suture can be applied both prophylactically and urgently with the expansion of
the cervical canal by more than 20 mm, prolapse of the fetal bladder.&nbsp;The
suture is performed both under epidural anesthesia and under general anesthesia.&nbsp;</span><span
lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>At
36-38 weeks, the cerclage should be removed.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Possible Complications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
